{"title": "Hand of Death", "content": "A particular shot commonly used in action flicks, gangster movies, horror movies, and murder mysteries. All that is shown is An Insert of a hand or a pair of hands, and possibly the murder weapon itself. This gives a sense of building tension without revealing the murderer's identity. Sinister black gloves are optional.\n\nOften, the character is walking slowly \u2014 one might say... ominously \u2014 with a gun in his hand, held down by his side. He may well be wearing a trenchcoat.\n\nCommon in slasher films. Even more common in Giallo.\n\nNot to be confused with the Touch of Death or Finger Poke of Doom.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HandOfDeath", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheHouseByTheCemetery", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Psycho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/AnthonyPerkins", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/AShotInTheDark", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Clue", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheUsualSuspects", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/DarioArgento", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheBirdWithTheCrystalPlumage", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheSting", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheRadiolandMurders", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/RedDragon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/StrangeDays", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/StudentBodies", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/CircusOfFear", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Charade", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/IronMan3", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/KnifeForTheLadies", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheInitiation", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Madhouse1974", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheGraveyardBook", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BronBroen", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheDoctorBlakeMysteries", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DoctorWho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/FrontierCircus", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/JonathanCreek", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MidsomerMurders", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MissFishersMurderMysteries", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/MissMarple", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/PoliceSquad", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series